A driver has died in a crash involving a car and a lorry on the M54.  The crash happened between junctions 2 and 3 of the motorway near Brewood, Staffordshire, at about 18:30 GMT on Monday.The man who was driving the car died at the scene after paramedics found him in a critical condition, the ambulance service said.No other patients needed treatment after the crash, they added.The road was shut for several hours but the Central Motorways Policing Group has since confirmed it has reopened.
